metadata.name: Overgrowth #16
metadata.description:
This work is an exploration of random growth focused on three interconnected elements. The first is a randomly moving brush, the second is one is an alternating overlay of white and black circles along bezier points between brush movements, and the final one being a continually decreasing brush size.

The overall result gives a complex scribble art effect. 

Created with p5.js

metadata.name: Liaisons Dangereuses #44
metadata.description:
"Liaisons dangereuses" is a creative exploration of implausible relations between figurative art and poetry. Our AI poet learned on the basis of texts about artists and their work. It memorized all subtleties of a language designed to describe visual emotions and artworks. This language is the tool for creating countless poems about artistic concepts, which range from techniques to materials to artists, etc. But the link is two-sided: if the poet is fed by art language, the concepts expressed by poems do, in turn, influence the appearance of the artwork. Color palettes, pattern types and the flow of the graphic composition are indeed determined by the semantics of the poem.
In each minting, the poet will produce either a short poem (a iambic 5-7-5 haiku  or a iambic cinquain according to Adelaide Crapsey style) or a single verse (either an alexandrine, or a iambic pentameter or an anapestic tetrameter). There are 625 artistic concepts that can trigger a poem, and each concept can generate countless different semantically coherent poems. The poet is completely "unchained": contents might be peaceful harmonic assertions as well as embarrassing, politically incorrect claims.

You can save to file the image by pressing the "s" key.

This language is the tool for creating countless poems about artistic concepts, which range from techniques to materials to artists, etc. But the link is two-sided: if the poet is fed by art language, the concepts expressed by poems do, in turn, influence the appearance of the artwork. Color palettes, pattern types and the flow of the graphic composition are indeed determined by the semantics of the poem.
In each minting, the poet will produce either a short poem (a iambic 5-7-5 haiku  or a iambic cinquain according to Adelaide Crapsey style) or a single verse (either an alexandrine, or a iambic pentameter or an anapestic tetrameter). There are 625 artistic concepts that can trigger a poem, and each concept can generate countless different semantically coherent poems. The poet is completely "unchained": contents might be peaceful harmonic assertions as well as embarrassing, politically incorrect claims.

You can save to file the image by pressing the "s" key.

metadata.name: Rug of imagination #29
metadata.description:
I recently faced covid, I can say it was one of the worst moments of my life, I questioned my sanity and if I would stay alive. What comforted me was to remember my childhood, my past, and I remembered the rugs I used to sit on to play or listen to stories, it is amazing how in the day to day we forget the little things in life that make us happy, sometimes we stop living to just survive.

Artwork made with p5.js and p5.scribbles

metadata.name: Provence #476
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise
